        In another touching post that resonated with fans, she also opened up about what it was like to break the news of her illness to her 12-year-old son. "As much as we wanted to protect him, we knew it was important to tell him the full facts [...] He took the news so maturely...and instantly became a source of strength and positivity for me," she wrote on Instagram in July. 
    
        
